00:00:14.010 --> 00:00:18.990
Simply put, computer and network
security refers to the practices

00:00:19.020 --> 00:00:21.660
and all the fancy technology we use.

00:00:21.939 --> 00:00:26.980
To protect our computer systems,
networks, and precious data from any

00:00:26.980 --> 00:00:29.830
unauthorized access, use, or drama.

00:00:30.340 --> 00:00:34.510
It's about ensuring the
confidentiality, integrity, and

00:00:34.510 --> 00:00:36.820
availability of our information.

00:00:37.330 --> 00:00:42.550
Think of it as building a solid digital
fortress around your assets to keep them

00:00:42.550 --> 00:00:45.340
safe from all kinds of digital goons.

00:00:46.000 --> 00:00:49.360
Key concepts in computer and
network security include.

00:00:50.215 --> 00:00:54.985
First we have confidentiality,
which is just a fancy way of saying

00:00:55.105 --> 00:00:59.875
your information is for your eyes
only, and those you authorize.

00:01:00.235 --> 00:01:02.095
It keeps your secret safe.

00:01:02.605 --> 00:01:07.255
Then there's integrity, which means
making sure your data is accurate.

00:01:07.340 --> 00:01:11.420
And complete, and nobody has
messed with it without permission.

00:01:11.810 --> 00:01:14.090
Finally, we have availability.

00:01:14.420 --> 00:01:18.560
This means authorized users can get
their data whenever they need it

00:01:18.740 --> 00:01:20.960
without any annoying disruptions.

00:01:21.260 --> 00:01:27.230
This is the famous CIA Triad
Common Threats and Attacks Now

00:01:27.230 --> 00:01:28.910
